   <narrative xml:lang="EN">National Civil Rights Museum COVID and Racism</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">COVID-19 and racism have collided. Young people-the protest marchers of today mirror those of yesterday as experienced in the National Civil Rights Museum at the Lorraine Motel. The difference TODAY is the magnitude of the marches and the diversity of people voicing their anger. Protestors are drawn to the Museum where the balcony of Room 306 stands as a testament to Dr. King and as a call to action for this generation to be the change makers of today, many have answered the call and you can too</narrative>
  </description>
